senses.sense_definition: A complex whole formed by a combination of various parts or elements.

examples.text: The historian described the <w>complexus</w> of events that led to the revolution.
Understanding the social <w>complexus</w> requires studying both economic and cultural factors.

senses.sense_definition: A large muscle of the back of the neck that extends from the spine to the head.

examples.text: Tension in the <w>complexus</w> can often result in severe headaches.
The physical therapist massaged the <w>complexus</w> muscle to relieve the patient's neck pain.
